tResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eexternal urethral sphincter\u003C/strong\u003E is found within the deep perineal pouch, also known as the urogenital diaphragm. This muscular structure works alongside the deep transverse perineal muscle and compressor urethrae to maintain urinary continence.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eischiocavernosus\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Ebulbospongiosus\u003C/strong\u003E, and \u003Cstrong\u003Esuperficial transverse perineal\u003C/strong\u003E muscles are components of the superficial perineal pouch rather than the deep compartment. The \u003Cstrong\u003Elevator ani\u003C/strong\u003E muscle is positioned superiorly as a key component of the pelvic diaphragm, helping to support the pelvic organs.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The external urethral sphincter is located in the deep perineal pouch (urogenital diaphragm) in females","The deep perineal pouch contains the external urethral sphincter, deep transverse perineal muscle, and compressor urethrae","The superficial perineal pouch contains the ischiocavernosus, bulbospongiosus, and superficial transverse perineal muscles"],"references":["Evans, T. J., \u0026 Ganjam, V. K. (2017). Reproductive anatomy and physiology. In Reproductive and Developmental Toxicology (pp. 7-37). Academic Press","Bolla SR, Hoare BS, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Abdomen and Pelvis: Deep Perineal Space. [Updated 2023 Aug 8]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538272/","Kovacs, W. J., \u0026 Ojeda, S. R. (Eds.). (2012). Textbook of endocrine physiology. OUP USA"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96406"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15680"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"96406","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/ap